==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Doit
<hw>Doit</hw> <pr>(doit)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>duit</ets>,
Icel. <ets>pveit</ets>, prop., a piece cut off. See <er>Thwaite</er> a
piece of ground, <er>Thwite</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small Dutch
coin, worth about half a farthing; also, a similar small coin once used
in Scotland; hence, any small piece of money.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A thing of small value; <as>as, I care not a
<ex>doit</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doitkin</ent>⟦br⟧
